Important legal

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________


spiderFramework is an intranet oriented PHP Framework, altrought it can be used in
another scenarios, it had grown naturally around the necessities of intranets
because the main author had always made intranets with it and his previous
frameworks.

The design is centered around Page Patterns (Row, Listings, Edit's, Forms, etc..)
that can be extended and of course you can make your own patterns.

The first public review is still in development but can be used seamlessly 
with your Devidas precautions and after review and authorized by the developer.

spiderFramework is a development of the aforementioned author and @bboymay (spiderMay) @arthurlinux 
and if you wish a copy of this framework to create your Applications must become attached to the 
regulation issued by the author almost 2-based general rules and a series of slogans such as convention, 
The basic rules are listed below:

1 .- If you want to create free applications development spiderframework is free, 
	 if you feed him for a better performance, make it known to the authors and 
	 share your knowledge and improvements

2 .- If you develop applications under the framework of spiderFramework, 
	 then you'll be forced to give back financially to the authors of spiderFramework as alias 
	 @bboymay (spiderMay) and @ arthurlinux, otherwise you simply need to run the script to remove 
	 the framework, it is not your authorship, or are interested in meeting the guidelines.

[Paragraph] 
	If Alcabes 3 months of development or publication of your applications, you have not informed 
	of your commercial and private activity as to spiderFramework, this will be eliminated if only 
	hoping not to cause discomfort of any kind and if they do Communicate immediately with the lead 
	authors to reach an agreement and solve your inconveniences, being as legal evidence for this 
	file disclaims any responsibility

The convention's must read in the documentation folder

